1. if checks the first condition
   else if checks the next condition if the first one is false
2. When you are checking one value with many choices
3. code:
   for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
  if (i === 4) {
    break;
  }
  console.log(i);
}
#output:1 2 3
4. while checks before running
   do-while checks after running
5. continue will skip the current step and goes to the next one in the loop

